name: How to Make Ofada Stew (Nigerian Ofada Sauce recipe)
description: In this ofada sauce recipe, I share how to make Ofada stew, a Western Nigerian stew commonly eaten with a locally grown rice called ofada rice. Ofada rice and stew is one of those delicious native savory dishes that packs a major punch as it is flavored with smoked died shrimp, and fermented locust beans (iru).

name: How to Make Ofada Stew (Nigerian Ofada Sauce recipe)
description: In this ofada sauce recipe, I share how to make Ofada stew, a Western Nigerian stew commonly eaten with a locally grown rice called ofada rice. Ofada rice and stew is one of those delicious native savory dishes that packs a major punch as it is flavored with smoked died shrimp, and fermented locust beans (iru).

name: How to Make Ofada Stew (Nigerian Ofada Sauce recipe)
description: In this ofada sauce recipe, I share how to make Ofada stew, a Western Nigerian stew commonly eaten with a locally grown rice called ofada rice. Ofada rice and stew is one of those delicious native savory dishes that packs a major punch as it is flavored with smoked died shrimp, and fermented locust beans (iru).

name: Nigerian Doughnuts (Fried Donut Recipe Without Eggs)
description: The Nigerian doughnut has been a favorite of mine since I was a kid. These jam filled donuts have a soft and chewy texture, are lightly sweet, and absolutely delicious! name: Efo Riro: Nigerian Spinach Stew (Yoruba Vegetable Soup)
description: This Nigerian spinach stew, also called vegetable soup and natively known as "Efo Riro" is guaranteed to be one of the most savory and delicious spinach recipes you will ever taste!

name: Eat Ramen Noodles Like An African
Plantain Chips: 9 Secrets to Crispy, Sweet Chips Every Time
description: Here are my secrets to fool-proof, extra crispy plantain chips. These easy tips work all the time so save your money and forget the store bought plantain chips!

name: Coconut Fried Rice
description: Rice cooked in broth and coconut milk with lots of vegetables and protein. The end product is an enticing combination of textures, colors, and flavors. It smells heavenly and tastes even better!

name: Beans and Beef Combo
description: : Looking for a simple yet delicious meal? This beans and ground beef recipe is your go-to for a quick, nutritious dinner that the whole family will love.

name: Ikokore/Ifokore – Water Yam Pottage
description: Ikokore is a delectable traditional Nigerian delicacy made from a blend of grated water yam, cooked with fish, meat, and assorted vegetables in a savory, spicy broth. It’s a cherished treat in many homes, bringing comfort and sweet flavor in one plate.

name: Nigerian Style Pancakes
description: The African Pancake is a straightforward yet delicious meal. Just like most Pancakes, the African pancake consists of ”dry ingredients” – Flour, leavening, and sugar and ”wet ingredients” – milk, Egg, and butter. However, it’s unique texture is what makes it different from the fluffy Pancake.

name: Easy Peanut Butter Soup
description: Like Peanut Butter? You’re going to love this peanut butter soup recipe. This soup is not only easy to make but incredibly good! Your family and friends will be proud of you.

name: Grilled Corn
description: Get smoky and charred flavors by grilling fresh corn, and enhance the taste with butter, salt, and optional toppings. Perfect for summer barbecues!

name: Stick Meat recipe – How to make the Nigerian Stick Meat
description: Stick Meat is a very delicious and colorful Nigerian Snack. The color and the smell triggers the taste buds. It’s often served in Nigerian parties and it’s also a street food in some parts of Nigeria. Here is how it’s made.

name: African Masa Recipe
description: The Nigerian Northerners are known for their healthy and delicious meals and I was not too surprised the very first time I ate Masa.

name: Gbegiri Soup
description: Gbegiri is a delicious West African soup enjoyed mostly by the Yoruba people. This recipe serves 6 to 8 people and is perfect for those who love African cuisine or want to try something new. Let's go to the southwestern part of Nigeria!

name: Nyama Choma A Delectable East African Delight
description: Enjoy your taste of East Africa with this delicious and flavorful nyama choma recipe! A Deliciously Succulent Grilled Meat that is perfect for any occasion.

name: Beef Party-style Jollof Rice
description: This is an incredibly easy, but delicious recipe. The uniqueness of this jollof rice lies in the roasting of the bell peppers, tomatoes, onions, and garlic. This brings an additional depth of flavor to the meal. If you’re looking for a Jollof Rice recipe that will be the star of the show, this is it!

name: How to make Jollof Spaghetti – Jollof Spaghetti Recipe
description: Are you bored with everyday spaghetti and sauce try this Jollof Spaghetti – An easy to make recipe with just a couple of ingredients and your lunch or dinner table is set.

name: Chicken Samosa
description: Chicken Samosa – Let’s talk about Samosas; these little but tasty pastry can either be fried or baked and it can serve as an appetizer, entree or snacks.

name: Amala
description: Today, we will be taking you to the southwestern part of Nigeria, where we will be learning how to prepare an African delicacy called Amala. Whether you are a fan of African cuisine or just looking to try something new, Amala is definitely worth a try.

name: African Spaghetti Sauce with Meatballs
description: This African Spaghetti Sauce with Meatballs is a savory and flavorful dish that offers a unique taste of Africa. It combines the ingredients of bell peppers, tomatoes, onions, scotch bonnet, thyme and curry powder, and is rounded off with succulent, juicy meatballs. This dish is perfect dish for any special occasion, or even just a weeknight dinner.

name: Berbere Spice
description: A flavorsome meal does wonders for the soul. Adding the classic and traditional Berbere Spice to your meal is a sure way of making your meal more delicious and full of flavor. This spice blend will give your meal that spicy and zesty kick. You will find yourself adding this to almost all your meals.

name: Niter Kibbeh
description: Niter Kibbeh – Ethiopian spiced clarified butter condiments used in various dishes, from stews and soups to sautés and marinades. Make this authentic flavor from your kitchen and enjoy.

name: Peri Peri Sauce
description: Get ready to fire up your dinner with the tantalizing taste of Peri Peri Sauce!

name: Suya
description: Skewers of thinly sliced meat, oven-grilled and doused with yaji spice. There's nothing quite like suya. It's unique taste is irresistible! It's lip-smacking, finger-licking good!

name: Meat Floss (Beef Floss)
description: Are you ready for the next level of meat floss? Then, we present Dambu Nama, a dried shredded beef that is so delicious.

name: Oven-baked Yuca Fries
description: Yuca Fries are very easy to prepare, they are immensely satisfying, with cotton soft melting interior and super crusty exterior. They are as good as potato fries but they have more character.

name: Chakalaka – South African Dish
description: Chakalaka is a traditional South African vegetable relish that is spicy, tangy, and full of flavor. Here is how you can make it at home.

name: 60 Nigerian Recipes You Need To Try
description: Food is part of our identity in Nigeria. We have rich, delicious, and nutrient-dense foods that fully satisfy the soul and the body. It is always a delight to make a variety of these dishes. For Nigerians, nothing tastes better than our traditional meal, no matter where we find ourselves in the world. You’ll find different types of Nigerian soups, stews, snacks, and swallows here. Enjoy!

name: How to make Eba
description: Eba is a staple Nigerian food made with garri (Cassava flakes) and boiling water to form a dough. It is not eaten alone, so it is served with Nigerian soups like okro, egusi, efo riro, and ewedu (jute leave soup).

name: Yam pottage/Yam Porridge (Asaro) Recipe
description: The Nigerian Yam pottage/Yam Porridge (Asaro) Recipe – Asaro which is also known as Yam pottage or Yam porridge is a very delicious Yam recipe.

name: How to make Moin Moin/Moi Moi
description: Moin Moin/Moi moi – This recipe makes a delicious savory moi moi. Soft and moist but not mushy. It is firm enough to hold it's shape. I'm sure you will love it!

name: Harissa Chicken Wings
description: These Harissa Chicken Wings are hot and spicy, but they're also packed with flavor. The perfect balance of sweet, salty and spicy makes these wings stand out from the rest.

name: Grilled Plantains
description: Grilled Plantains: A staple of street affairs in West Africa. It’s a very simple, straightforward, and satisfying recipe. If you’ve never tried grilled plantains, let this recipe be a sweet introduction.

name: Ewedu Soup Recipe
description: Ewedu is very popular not only in west Africa but in the Middle East, East Africa, and North Africa. It is, without a doubt, one of the easiest Nigerian soups to cook.

name: Fried plantains
description: Fried plantains – This is a sweet-savory dish that features thick slices of ripe plantains lightly salted and deep-fried in oil till golden brown. The result is a caramel-like brown crust that is savory-sweet and a soft and very sweet interior.

name: Suya spice
description: Suya spice –  Hello, spicy food lovers add bold seasoning and flavor to just about any dish with this fantastic Suya Spice Mix! Delicious on fish, chicken, potatoes, and more!

name: Healthy Shakshuka Recipe
description: Shakshuka is a hearty skillet meal made of open-faced eggs cooked in a thick, savory tomato-pepper sauce. It is simple, delicious, and easy to prepare.

name: Homemade Harissa Recipe
description: Homemade Harissa Recipe: Harissa paste is a versatile North African condiment made with dried chilies, garlic, olive oil, and spices. It can be used as an accompaniment to grilled meats and fish or simply added to soups and stews for an extra kick. This recipe is super simple to make, only taking 5 minutes at the most!

name: Nigerian Tomato Stew
description: Nigerian Beef Stew: A classic rich aromatic tomato Nigerian stew. It is delicious, nutritious, and easy to make. All you need is a big pot and about an hour of your time.

name: African Buns
description: Nigerian buns –  Small golden balls of pure goodness, slightly crispy on the outside and perfectly soft on the inside.

name: Matoke
description: Matoke is a simple, healthy, and delicious one-pot East African dish made from green bananas. Easy to prepare but can fill you up for hours! Great for lunch or dinner.

name: African Irio (Mashed potatoes, corn and peas)
description: This medley of Potatoes, corn, and peas is very delicious, very filling, and perfect for a mid-week comfort food dinner.

name: Top South African Foods to try
description: Here are some of the top South African recipes that are sure to become favorites with you and your family members – they’re always tasty, filling, and of course completely authentic.

name: Taro fries
description: These fresh, crispy and irresistible fries are simple to make and perfect for adding to any meal.

name: Injera
description: Injera is a soft, thin pancake-like flatbread made from fermented teff batter. A staple food in Ethiopia/Eritrea usually used as a serving base for scooping stews, meat, and vegetables like Doro wat, gomen wat, and much more.

name: A Taste of Ethiopia with Gomen Wat
description: Looking for a delicious taste of Ethiopian cuisine? Gomen wat is the Ethiopian version of collard greens, and it’s delectably delicious. Here’s how to make it.

name: Doro wat
description: Doro wat is an incredibly fragrant, spicy, flavorful, rich slow-cooked Ethiopian chicken stew mostly eaten for special occasions and family gatherings.

name: African pepper sauce
description: African pepper sauce is a hot and spicy sauce made with habaneros, tomatoes, ginger, and strong onion and garlic notes. This African condiment is so addictive, and you will be happy to join the ranks of your must-have condiments!

name: Hot pot potatoes
description: Hot pot potatoes are nutritious, delicious, and filling! It is perfect as a comforting and complete family meal or an impressive addition to a dinner party.

name: Easy Homemade Chicken Shawarma
description: Chicken Shawarma is a Middle Eastern Recipe and Nigeria’s version adds some flare to it.You can prepare Shawarma using a rotisserie, gill it outdoor or bake in the Oven. Middle Eastern spices are rare in Nigeria, though one can recreate Shawarma using common spices.

name: Fufu
description: Fufu – A filling side dish, simple and satisfying and easy to prep. The perfect accompaniment to soups/stews and protein.

name: Pawpaw Juice
description: Wonderfully refreshing and easy to make homemade pawpaw juice recipe. It is made in blender only, a must-try not only during the summer season but all seasons.

name: Plantain Puff Puff
description: Plantain Puff Puff – Nothing beats homemade Puff Puffs! They’re fresh, soft, and chewy. Not to mention they are super easy to make and absolutely delicious. You will get addicted!

name: African Puff puff Recipe
description: Puff puff is a deep-fried dough. They are made from yeast dough, shaped into balls and deep-fried until golden brown. It has a doughnut-like texture but slightly more chewy. It is a very common snack eaten by so many countries but with different names and a little bit of variation in the mode of preparation.

name: Senegalese Poulet Yassa
description: Enjoy the flavors of West Africa with this Senegalese Poulet Yassa made from chicken pieces marinated overnight with lots of onions, some mustard, and a bit of lemon juice.

name: Banga soup
description: Banga soup is one of the best nourishing soup you can make with palm nut. All it takes is an assortment of spice flavorings, an assortment of meat and fish, and finishing it off with a touch of beletete to elevate this soup. It’s an easy recipe that delivers terrific results!

name: Peri-Peri Chicken (Piri-Piri Chicken)
description: This spicy African chicken dish is made with birds-eye chilies, herbs, and spices. It's super easy to prepare!

name: Ewa riro
description: Ewa riro is a delicious one-pot Nigerian delicacy that is easy to prepare but yields a rich flavor. This is truly the best-stewed beans recipe that you will ever taste. Plus it’s incredibly economical.

name: Chicken Fried Rice
description: This version of the Nigerian fried Rice dish delivers a delicious flavor with minimal efforts. It comes together in a little time with minimal effort making it perfect for a weeknight.

name: Crispy Spring Roll
description: Crispy Spring Roll - These spring rolls are light and very crisp with savory beef and vegetable fillings. You can read my spring roll sheet story here.

name: Black Eyed Peas Salad with simple vinaigrette dressing
description: This salad is loaded with lots of vegetables, inexpensive to make, easy to prep, and absolutely delicious.

name: Kachumbari
description: Kachumbari is a simple, light, and easy-to-make east African salad made with onions, tomatoes, cucumbers, salt, pepper, and lemon dressing – a fresh, tart salad with a little kick to it.

name: East African Pilau
description: East African Pilau is a traditional, beautiful fragrant rice dish made with many aromatic spices that adds an amazing depth of flavor to the rice. It can be made with either beef or chicken.

name: Okro pepper soup
description: Okro pepper soup is a simple, spicy, delicious Nigerian soup that originated in the Southern part of Nigeria where it’s commonly referred to as Igbagba Ofofo or Gbagbafo by the natives.

name: Nigerian Pepper Sauce recipe – Ata dindin
description: Nigerian Pepper Sauce popularly known as Ata dindin, is a hearty stew that warms you from your head to your toes — made with bell peppers, Tomatoes, Onion, ginger, habaneros, chili flakes, garlic, and ginger. It’s fiery red, bold, and spicy.

name: Grilled Catfish
description: African Grilled Catfish – The process of smoking or drying fish eliminates moisture from the fish, adds flavor and helps in the preserving process. The dried fish turns out really tasty, it imparts a smoky flavor into anything you are cooking. So good!

name: Chicken pepper soup
description: Sometimes, a comforting bowl of soup is all you need. This easy to put together chicken pepper soup is loaded with spicy, bold, and hearty flavors. It’s so easy to make and you can hardly go wrong putting this together.

name: Vegetable Couscous
description: This easy one-pot Vegetable Couscous recipe is loaded with highly nutritious vegetables amongst other ingredients. It’s Fluffy, fragrant, and tasty with a kiss of warm flavors.

name: Okro soup
description: Okro soup is a very popular and delicious stew that is loved by the majority of the people, in West Africa, especially if cooked well.

name: Ogbono Soup
description: Ogbono soup is a delectable Nigerian concoction soup and it's super easy to prepare. It's a thick and hearty stew made with Ogbono seeds (wild mango seeds) loaded with meats and fish simmered in a light delicious broth.

name: Pounded Yam
description: Pounded Yam is a staple in many African homes, but it is not usually eaten by itself, it is often paired with many delicious African soups, and stews like Egusi, okra soup, Jute leaves soup (Ewedu), or Stewed Spinach (Efo Riro).

name: Salmon Stew
description: This hearty Salmon stew is a full-flavored stew. It’s a warm, hearty, spicy, savory, delicious dish that pretty much everyone loves. You will enjoy this boldly flavored fish stew and you will be pleased to add this to your repertoire.

name: East African Chapati Recipe – How to make Chapati
description: East African Chapati is a beautiful unleavened flat Bread eaten in East Africa in Countries like Burundi Uganda, Mozambique, Kenya,… What I like about this Bread is how soft it is and it goes along with a lot of meals

name: Chicken Vegetable Couscous
description: Chicken Vegetable Couscous: A blend of Scotch bonnet, Garlic, Onion, bell peppers, and spices adds a touch Savory and spicy to this meal. It's full of flavor and really quick to make, this meal will be a winner with all the family.

name: Nigerian Fried Rice Recipe
description: The Nigerian fried rice is a staple lunch, dinner, and even party dish in Nigeria. Very simple yet delicious recipe. This version uses mixed vegetables and Beef liver; you can use Shrimp or any protein you’d like. You can omit the beef liver if you love to make vegan fried rice.

name: Plantain Pancakes
description: Plantain pancakes – These are ultimate comfort food made from plantains and a few other ingredients. They are very light and tender almost like the French crepes. However, the process involved in making these pancakes are not as intimidating as that of the French crepes.

name: Oven baked Jollof Rice
description: Here is another take on Jollof Rice, one of the most famous West Africans one pot meal - Simplicity, is what sets apart the stove top from the oven baked method of cooking Jollof rice.

name: West African Peanut Soup
description: West African Peanut soup or Groundnut stew is a staple in most African cuisine as well as some other cultures like Taiwan in East Asia and Virginia in the states.  It is warm, nourishing and full of flavors. It is also very versatile which makes it perfect for any season of the year.

name: Nigerian Egg Roll Recipe
description: Boiled egg wrapped in a mass of dough and deep-fried. Easy to prepare, inexpensive, and very delicious. It can be eaten as breakfast, an appetizer, or snack with hot sauce or ketchup.

name: Coconut Rice (African style)
description: A savory side dish made with rice, cooked in aromatic coconut milk. It is so rich, luscious and bursting with aromatic coconut flavors. You will be surprised that a Rice recipe this simple has so much flavor.

name: Chin chin
description: Chin chin - This snack is a very popular Nigerian snack that doesn't last on the Table at all if done right and different people have their preferences ranging from the really hard ones to the really soft ones. My preference is just in-between and thats the recipe I have shared below. However, I have given some tips below on how you can make the soft or the hard version so you could choose your preference.

name: Plantain Pancakes with Spicy Maple Syrup and Peanuts
description: These delicious plantain pancakes are topped off with a spicy mix of chili, maple syrup and crushed peanuts to produce a delicious treat!

name: Afang Soup Recipe
description: Afang soup, eaten by Efik and Ibibio people of Nigeria is a delicious stew made with Afang leaves and a leafy vegetable called waterleaf.

name: Fonio Porridge/Acha Pudding: A Super-Grain Breakfast Cereal!
description: Fonio is a gluten-free, nutritious, super grain grown natively in West Africa, and is featured in this delicious and highly nutritious Acha pudding or fonio porridge breakfast cereal!

name: Mixed Seafood Coconut Fried Rice Recipe
description: In this delicious mixed seafood coconut fried rice recipe I'll be showing how to cook coconut fried rice with a seafood medley featuring a mix of fresh crab meat, shrimp, calamari and fresh homemade coconut milk!

name: Peppered Snail Recipe
description: The spicy, chewy goodness of peppered snail consists of boiled snails sautéed in onions, peppers and spice. This spicy Nigerian snail dish is quite easy to prepare and is a guilty pleasure of a lot of Nigerian homes

name: Nigerian Spring Rolls Recipe
description: These spicy and delicious Nigerian spring rolls are an essential favorite of Nigerian small chops (hors d'oeuvres) commonly served in Nigerian parties and events.

name: Edikaikong Soup Recipe (Edikang Ikong Soup)
description: Edikang Ikong Soup is a highly nutritious, delicious and savory vegetable soup natively prepared using ‘ugwu’ (the native name for fluted pumpkin leaves) and Malabar spinach (locally called water leaf in Nigeria).

name: Fonio Grits and Shrimp
description: If you're a fan of classic grits, you'll love this savory fonio grits and shrimp, which is more nutritious and packs a seafood flavor punch!

name: Nigerian Tomato Stew (Nigerian Red Stew) Recipe
description: This Nigerian red stew recipe features my favorite Nigerian tomato stew using farm raised ram meat which adds a distinct, delicious gamey flavor!

name: How to Make Ofada Stew (Nigerian Ofada Sauce recipe)
description: In this ofada sauce recipe, I share how to make Ofada stew, a Western Nigerian stew commonly eaten with a locally grown rice called ofada rice. Ofada rice and stew is one of those delicious native savory dishes that packs a major punch as it is flavored with smoked died shrimp, and fermented locust beans (iru).

name: How to Braise Meat Properly for West African Stews/Soups
description: Here's a little deep dive into how to braise meat properly when preparing to make stews and soups. With these clear steps, you can braise any amount of meat you have to get the best flavor out of it.

name: Nigerian Doughnuts (Fried Donut Recipe Without Eggs)
description: The Nigerian doughnut has been a favorite of mine since I was a kid. These jam filled donuts have a soft and chewy texture, are lightly sweet, and absolutely delicious! In my homemade vegan donuts' recipe, I'll be sharing with you how to make Nigerian doughnut without eggs and still nail its taste and fluffy texture!

name: Plantain Pancakes with Spicy Maple Syrup and Peanuts
description: These delicious plantain pancakes are topped off with a spicy mix of chili, maple syrup and crushed peanuts to produce a delicious treat!

name: Afang Soup Recipe
description: Afang soup, eaten by Efik and Ibibio people of Nigeria is a delicious stew made with Afang leaves and a leafy vegetable called waterleaf.

name: Fonio Porridge/Acha Pudding: A Super-Grain Breakfast Cereal!
description: Fonio is a gluten-free, nutritious, super grain grown natively in West Africa, and is featured in this delicious and highly nutritious Acha pudding or fonio porridge breakfast cereal!

name: Mixed Seafood Coconut Fried Rice Recipe
description: In this delicious mixed seafood coconut fried rice recipe I'll be showing how to cook coconut fried rice with a seafood medley featuring a mix of fresh crab meat, shrimp, calamari and fresh homemade coconut milk!

name: Peppered Snail Recipe
description: The spicy, chewy goodness of peppered snail consists of boiled snails sautéed in onions, peppers and spice. This spicy Nigerian snail dish is quite easy to prepare and is a guilty pleasure of a lot of Nigerian homes

name: Nigerian Spring Rolls Recipe
description: These spicy and delicious Nigerian spring rolls are an essential favorite of Nigerian small chops (hors d'oeuvres) commonly served in Nigerian parties and events.

name: Edikaikong Soup Recipe (Edikang Ikong Soup)
description: Edikang Ikong Soup is a highly nutritious, delicious and savory vegetable soup natively prepared using ‘ugwu’ (the native name for fluted pumpkin leaves) and Malabar spinach (locally called water leaf in Nigeria).

name: Fonio Grits and Shrimp
description: If you're a fan of classic grits, you'll love this savory fonio grits and shrimp, which is more nutritious and packs a seafood flavor punch!

name: Nigerian Tomato Stew (Nigerian Red Stew) Recipe
description: This Nigerian red stew recipe features my favorite Nigerian tomato stew using farm raised ram meat which adds a distinct, delicious gamey flavor!

name: How to Make Ofada Stew (Nigerian Ofada Sauce recipe)
description: In this ofada sauce recipe, I share how to make Ofada stew, a Western Nigerian stew commonly eaten with a locally grown rice called ofada rice. Ofada rice and stew is one of those delicious native savory dishes that packs a major punch as it is flavored with smoked died shrimp, and fermented locust beans (iru).

name: How to Braise Meat Properly for West African Stews/Soups
description: Here's a little deep dive into how to braise meat properly when preparing to make stews and soups. With these clear steps, you can braise any amount of meat you have to get the best flavor out of it.

name: Nigerian Doughnuts (Fried Donut Recipe Without Eggs)
description: The Nigerian doughnut has been a favorite of mine since I was a kid. These jam filled donuts have a soft and chewy texture, are lightly sweet, and absolutely delicious! In my homemade vegan donuts' recipe, I'll be sharing with you how to make Nigerian doughnut without eggs and still nail its taste and fluffy texture!

name: Zobo Drink (Sobolo/Bissap Juice): African Hibiscus Tea Recipe
description: Zobo drink, a sweet hibiscus/sorrel drink (also known in West Africa as bissap juice or Sobolo) is an African hibiscus tea made from dry sorrel leaves and with a special twist of mine is a refreshing way to welcome spring and summer!

name: Seafood Beniseed Soup
description: Beniseed or sesame seed, whichever name you choose to call it, makes one of the most delicious Nigerian stews ever, locally known as beniseed soup. Beniseed soup is a stew very similar in consistency to other nut or seed soups popular in Nigeria, but with its own distinct taste.

name: Nigerian Sausage Rolls with Chicken and Pancetta Filling
description: While traditional Nigerian sausage rolls are made with ground pork, this chicken and pancetta Nigerian sausage roll recipe elevates it beyond the popular classic making it perfect for celebrations or just a delicious snack! No matter the occasion, these homemade chicken sausage rolls will become an instant favorite!

name: Chick-Un Vegan Hand Pies
description: These addictive chick-un vegan hand pies are a chicken pie alternative I usually have on my Thanksgiving table, but you can certainly enjoy this anytime!

name: Miyan Taushe Recipe
description: This delicious pumpkin stew locally called Miyan Taushe is native to the Northern Nigeria and is commonly eaten with fufu/swallow, rice, and even naan bread.

name: Nigerian Beans Porridge
description: Nigerian beans porridge is the definition of complete comfort and can be paired with garri (cassava flakes), bread or ogi (fermented, corn starch porridge)

name: Plantain Bread Recipe
description: This delicious vegan plantain bread made with sweet plantains contains no eggs or dairy, tastes better than banana bread and is certain to appeal to even non-vegans like me!

name: Nigerian Akara Recipe
description: Akara (Accara) are tasty, deep fried, Nigerian brown bean or black eyed pea fritters that are also quite popular in West Africa and are served alone, with a side of starch, kaani or in a burger.

name: Moi Moi (Moin Moin) Recipe
description: This moi moi (moin moin) recipe features a Nigerian delicious, savory steamed bean pudding made from blended black eyed peas, peppers, onions, and spices

name: Groundnut Soup Recipe (Spicy Nigerian Peanut Stew)
description: Groundnut soup (also called peanut stew) is a common but delicious Nigerian delicacy which is commonly eaten with rice, a starch like eba or pounded yam.

name: Nigerian Chapman Drink Recipe
description: Nigeria's favorite non-alcoholic cocktail, this Nigerian chapman drink is a version of the refreshing beverage with more natural alternatives but the same great taste!

name: Crispy Fried Firecracker Shrimp Rolls Recipe
description: These crispy fried firecracker shrimp rolls are fun, delicious snacks with that satisfyingly crunchy snap and crackle that are commonly served as appetizers or "small chops" in weddings and parties.

name: Plantain Pancakes with Spicy Maple Syrup and Peanuts
description: These delicious plantain pancakes are topped off with a spicy mix of chili, maple syrup and crushed peanuts to produce a delicious treat!

name: Afang Soup Recipe
description: Afang soup, eaten by Efik and Ibibio people of Nigeria is a delicious stew made with Afang leaves and a leafy vegetable called waterleaf.

name: Fonio Porridge/Acha Pudding: A Super-Grain Breakfast Cereal!
description: Fonio is a gluten-free, nutritious, super grain grown natively in West Africa, and is featured in this delicious and highly nutritious Acha pudding or fonio porridge breakfast cereal!

name: Mixed Seafood Coconut Fried Rice Recipe
